C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20traffic%20has%20surged%20in%20the%20last%20few%20months%2C%20largely%20because%20of%20its%20increased%20prominence%20in%20Google%20search%20results.%20In%20April%2C%20Business%20Insider's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-reddit-is-taking-over-google-right-now-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHugh%20Langley%20reported%20how%20Reddit%20is%20%26quot%3Btaking%20over%26quot%3B%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20search%20results%2C%20in%20large%20part%20because%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Fproducts%2Fsearch%2Fmore-content-by-people-for-people-in-search%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Google%20to%20prioritize%20%26quot%3Bhelpful%20content%2C%26quot%3B%20aka%20forum%20posts%20(Quora%2C%20the%20question-and-answer%20site%2C%20also%20has%20seen%20a%20big%20bump%20in%20traffic).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20denied%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20boost%20to%20Reddit%20had%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20its%20%2460%20million%20deal%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-train-ai-model-crazy-subreddit-posts-reddit-licensing-deal-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elicense%20Reddit%20data%20for%20use%20in%20Google's%20AI%20products%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fpersonal-tech%2Fcan-you-replace-google-search-with-reddit-i-tried-it-for-a-week-ea1f36c5%3Fmod%3Ddjem10point%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20noted%20this%20week%20that%20Reddit%20traffic%20is%20way%20up%2C%20boosted%20in%20part%20by%20people%20adding%20%26quot%3Breddit%26quot%3B%20to%20their%20Google%20search%20queries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpro.similarweb.com%2F%3Fsourcepage%3Dwebsite-analysis%26domain%3Dreddit.com%26action%3Dlite-redirect%26utm_medium%3Dpr%26utm_source%3Doutreach%23overview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESimiliarweb%2C%20a%20data%20analytics%20firm%2C%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Reddit's%20traffic%20surged%2039%25%20in%20May%20year-over-year%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20a%20HUGE%20increase.%20Way%2C%20way%20bigger%20than%20the%20other%20social%20media%20companies%2C%20which%20saw%20moderate%20increases%20or%20even%20decreases%20(sorry%2C%20Facebook).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FGm3G4%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Year-over-year%20social%20media%20web%20traffic%20growth%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22454%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Similarweb%2C%20the%20big%20driver%20of%20Reddit%20traffic%20is%20indeed%20organic%20search%2C%20aka%20Google.%20Reddit.com%20had%20about%20834.5%20million%20direct%20visits%20in%20April%20(this%20means%20people%20typed%20reddit.com%20into%20their%20browser)%2C%20but%201.3%20billion%20visits%20came%20from%20Google%20search%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%20at%20this%20chart%20of%20Reddit's%20global%20traffic%20for%20the%20last%20five%20years.%20For%20a%20company%20that%20has%20been%20around%20for%20almost%2020%20years%2C%20the%20sharp%20increase%20to%20the%20far%20right%20is%2C%20to%20use%20a%20data%20science%20term%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebanoodles%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FO5Sx8%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Reddit%20web%20traffic%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22441%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20few%20ways%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20this.%20One%20is%20that%20Reddit%20is%20a%20highly%20useful%20source%20of%20information%20from%20real%20humans%2C%20and%20people%20love%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20explanation%20is%20that%20Google's%20search%20results%20are%20so%20borked%20that%20people%2C%20desperate%20for%20a%20better%20search%20experience%2C%20are%20narrowing%20their%20queries%20to%20Reddit's%20archives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20third%2C%20less%20appealing%20option%20is%20that%20shady%20people%20are%20using%20Reddit%20as%20a%20dirty%20SEO%20trick%2C%20spamming%20smaller%20subreddits%20with%20with%20SEO-friendly%20affiliate%20links%20%E2%80%94%20and%20causing%20a%20moderation%20headache.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20be%20a%20combination%20of%20all%20three!%20Either%20way%2C%20Reddit%20is%20a%20traffic%20juggernaut%20now.%20Huh!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-traffic-surges-from-google-search-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718794381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fb5501895d82203032ceb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-traffic-surges-from-google-search-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Reddit's%20traffic%20was%20up%2039%25%20in%20May%20year-over-year.%20That's%20a%20huge%20increase%20for%20a%20platform%20that's%20been%20around%20for%20almost%2020%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22knotopoulos%40businessinsider.com%20(Katie%20Notopoulos)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-traffic-surges-from-google-search-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shanghai%20Film%20Festival%3A%20Malaysian%20Animation%20%E2%80%98Extinction%E2%80%99%20Inks%20First%20Rights%20Deals%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718794276000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FExtinction-Pic-5-3x2cr-res.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%2