ience%20with%20inpatient%20treatment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20after%20my%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffell-in-love-another-patient-psych-ward-rejected-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epsychiatric%20hospitalization%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Queens%2C%20New%20York%2C%20I%20returned%20to%20my%20job%20at%20an%20alcoholism%20treatment%20center%20in%20San%20Francisco.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20in%201975%2C%20I%20had%20a%20second%20manic%20episode%2C%20which%20landed%20me%20in%20Langley%20Porter%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ward's%20common%20area%20looked%20like%20a%20large%2C%20L-shaped%20living%20room%20with%20couches%2C%20chairs%2C%20coffee%20tables%2C%20a%20ping-pong%20table%2C%20and%20a%20large%20bin%20with%20arts%20and%20crafts%20supplies.%20Inside%20it%2C%20I%20saw%20yarn%20and%20knitting%20needles%2C%20among%20other%20supplies.%20The%20room's%20walls%20were%20in%20pale%2C%20pastel%20tones%3B%20the%20furnishings%20were%20clean%20and%20in%20good%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatients%20wore%20their%20own%20clothes%20and%20seemed%20mentally%20clear.%20All%20this%20felt%20good%2C%20yet%20I%20was%20shocked%20to%20be%20there.%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%2C%20see%20friends%2C%20and%20get%20my%20life%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd37fa83-a0fe-405b-8028-47ca58f2f979%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20first%20met%20Henry%20when%20I%20was%20a%20patient%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20played%20ping-pong%20with%20Henry%2C%20a%20stocky%2C%20lively%20patient%20around%20my%20age.%20He%20cracked%20jokes%20as%20he%20slammed%20back%20my%20shots.%20The%20score%20was%20close%20to%20even.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHey%2C%20where'd%20you%20learn%20to%20play%20so%20well%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20father%20taught%20me%20when%20I%20was%20a%20kid.%26quot%3B%20I%20pictured%20how%20Dad's%20eyes%20would%20light%20up%20when%20I%20surprised%20him%20with%20a%20good%20slam%20or%20shot%20back%20one%20of%20his.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHenry%20sent%20a%20high%20one%20my%20way%2C%20and%20I%20smashed%20it%20back.%20His%20mouth%20dropped%20open%20when%20the%20ball%20grazed%20the%20table's%20edge%20and%20landed%20at%20his%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I%20could%20learn%20some%20tricks%20from%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20lucky.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20having%20so%20much%20fun%20I%20almost%20forgot%20where%20I%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20your%20first%20time%20here%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20but%20I%20was%20at%20another%20place%20last%20year.%20It%20was%20awful.%20Langley%20Porter's%20a%20palace%20compared%20with%20that%20snake%20pit.%26quot%3B%20My%20stomach%20tightened%20at%20the%20thought%20of%20Elmhurst%3B%20then%20I%20relaxed%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3Eagain%20in%20the%20game's%20rhythm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20nodded.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20in%20worse%20too.%20This%20place%20is%20one%20of%20the%20better%20ones.%20It's%20like%20%E2%80%94%20smaller%2C%20more%20personal.%20Nicer%20atmosphere%2C%20if%20you%20know%20what%20I%20mean.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHey%2C%20you%20could%20write%20a%20tourist%20guidebook%20for%20the%20mentally%20ill%20and%20compare%20the%20facilities.%26quot%3B%20We%20both%20laughed.%20I%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20rate%20them%2C%20give%20them%20a%20different%20number%20of%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3Estars%20or%20diamonds%20for%20service%2C%20appearance%2C%20etcetera.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20I%20could%20compare%20the%20doctors%2C%20the%20food%2C%20the%20furniture%2C%20the%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20patients%2C%20visiting%20policies%2C%20bathrooms%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20laughed%20louder.%20%26quot%3BHa%2C%20ha!%20Hey%2C%20you%20crack%20me%20up.%20What%20did%20you%20say%20your%20name%20was%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarcia.%26quot%3B%20I%20surprised%20him%20with%20a%20slam%2C%20but%20he%20lobbed%20it%20back.%20He%20caught%20me%20off%20guard%3B%20I%20missed%2C%20and%20he%20won%20the%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%2C%20I%20took%20yarn%20from%20the%20bin%20and%20knitted%20a%20pillow%20cover%20in%20earth%20tones%2C%20like%20the%20pillow%20I'd%20given%20Doreen%20during%20my%20recent%20manic%20spree%20at%20work.%20The%20wool%20against%20my%20skin%20and%20the%20repetitive%20clicking%20of%20the%20knitting%20needles%20soothed%20me.%20I%20looked%20forward%20to%20finishing%20the%20pillow%20and%20sleeping%20with%20it%20at%20home%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversation%20flowed%20easily%20between%20patients.%20No%20one%20seemed%20too%20heavily%20medicated.%20It%20felt%20like%20a%20comfortable%20dormitory.%20Whatever%20happened%20to%20me%20that%20got%20me%20there%20seemed%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20months%20later%2C%20I%20had%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbipolar-disorder-manic-spending-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanic%20episode%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20started%20taking%20medication%20that%20stabilized%20me.%20Yet%2C%20it%20was%20too%20late%20for%20me%20to%20regain%20the%20respect%20of%20some%20coworkers%2C%20which%20made%20for%20a%20toxic%20work%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee1344ca-6440-4722-99a2-e1ebdc445937%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENone%20of%20my%20coworkers%20knew%20I'd%20been%20a%20psychiatric%20inpatient%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20I%20was%20recruited%20to%20my%20next%20job%20as%20a%20senior%20psychiatric%20social%20worker%20in%20San%20Francisco%20General%20Hospital's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpregnancy-mental-health-diagnosis-reproductive-psychiatrist-cost-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epsychiatric%20ward%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20my%20colleagues%20respected%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20wanting%20to%20be%20stigmatized%2C%20I%20told%20no%20one%20there%20that%20I'd%20been%20a%20psychiatric%20inpatient%20elsewhere.%20But%20something%20happened%20that%20almost%20blew%20my%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20patient%20caught%20my%20attention%20one%20day%20as%20I%20went%20to%20the%20ward's%20conference%20room.%20He%20looked%20vaguely%20familiar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHey!%26quot%3B%20he%20called%20out.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20I%20know%20you%20from%20somewhere%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20looked%20at%20him%20and%20felt%20a%20sinking%20feeling%20in%20my%20gut.%20%26quot%3BLangley%20Porter%2C%20that's%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20called%20out%20and%20laughed.%20%26quot%3BLangley%20Porter.%20Hey%2C%20how%20'bout%20that%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20Henry!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20one%20was%20in%20earshot.%20Wishing%20I%20could%20disappear%2C%20I%20looked%20at%20him%20blankly%2C%20like%20he%20was%20mistaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e21cf6a3-a863-4062-a42f-a88b67129d2e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20worried%20my%20cover%20would%20be%20blown%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah!%20I%20remember%20you.%20Don't%20you%20remember%20me%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20smiled.%20Was%20he%20accusing%20or%20just%20being%20friendly%3F%20Too%20off-balance%20to%20know%2C%20I%20stood%20frozen%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPing-pong!%20I%20remember%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20loudly.%20%26quot%3BDon't%20you%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20lied%2C%20shrugging%20my%20shoulders%20and%20avoiding%20his%20eyes.%20I%20sensed%20he%20saw%20through%20me%2C%20and%20I%20rushed%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20relieved%20when%20they%20didn't%20assign%20Henry%20to%20my%20team.%20But%20I%20felt%20uneasy%2C%20like%20a%20potential%20blackmail%20victim%2C%20until%20his%20discharge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudiously%2C%20I%20avoided%20him%2C%20quivering%20inside%2C%20wondering%2C%20%3Cem%3EDid%20he%20tell%20anyone%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20time%2C%20I%20forgot%20about%20Henry%20%E2%80%94%20until%20he%20was%20readmitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHi%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20that%20time.%20I%20heard%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can%20ruin%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20to%20say%2C%20%3Cem%3Eplease%20don't%20tell%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20I%20was%20still%20pretending%20I'd%20never%20seen%20him%20before.%20Then%20I%20saw%20his%20name%20on%20my%20list%20of%20patients%20on%20the%20large%20whiteboard%20that%20paired%20patients%20with%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fhow-to-find-a-therapist%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprimary%20therapists%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Cem%3ENo%2C%20no%2C%20no!%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20become%20friendly%20with%20Barbara%2C%20a%20psychology%20intern%20in%20her%20forties%20on%20a%20different%20team.%20I%20considered%20her%20mature%20and%20trustworthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoping%20she%20wouldn't%20ask%20why%2C%20and%20with%20knots%20in%20my%20stomach%2C%20I%20told%20Barbara%20privately%20that%20I%20wasn't%20comfortable%20being%20Henry's%20therapist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'll%20take%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20like%20it%20was%20no%20big%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThank%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20gasped%2C%20touched%20by%20her%20easy%20generosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20wondered%20if%20Henry%20had%20revealed%20my%20secret.%20Could%20someone%20in%20a%20psychotic%20state%20exercise%20discretion%3F%20Had%20he%20relished%20saying%3A%20%3Cem%3EShe's%20as%20crazy%20as%20the%20rest%20of%20us%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDid%20Barbara%20know%3F%20Did%20everyone%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20discharge%2C%20I%20waited%20for%20the%20proverbial%20other%20shoe%20to%20drop%2C%20for%20the%20next%20time%20he'd%20show%20up%20on%20the%20ward.%20But%20I%20never%20saw%20him%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EExcerpted%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D0ee69cf428c3d7dac1508c604970841d4e2733e9fd9633