arget%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20taken%20by%20an%20Everglades%20National%20Park%20tourist%20named%20Alyssa.%20It%20shows%20a%20group%20of%20tourists%20standing%20a%20few%20feet%20away%20from%20an%20alligator%20crossing%20a%20path%20with%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20turtle%20snapped%20between%20its%20teeth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%20one%20child%20was%20among%20the%20tourists%2C%20the%20video%20shows.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC5x4XMtA73y%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20encounter%20shared%20on%20her%20personal%20Instagram%20account%2C%20the%20person%20who%20captured%20the%20incident%20said%20the%20people%20in%20the%20video%20were%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20close.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20isn't%20worth%20getting%20attacked%20and%20the%20alligator%20having%20to%20suffer%20because%20you%20refuse%20to%20take%205%20steps%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NPS%20recommends%20keeping%20a%20safe%20distance%20from%20alligators%20in%20the%20Everglades%2C%20roughly%20between%2015%20and%2020%20feet%2C%20which%20is%20farther%20than%20what%20appeared%20to%20be%20the%20case%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIn%20April%2C%20a%20man%20was%20charged%20with%20drunkenly%20harassing%20a%20herd%20of%20bison%20in%20Yellowstone.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yellowstone%20Bison%20shutterstock%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F527c06aa6bb3f7e53fdf173a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20Prince%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20NPS%2C%20park%20officials%20responded%20to%20a%20report%20in%20April%20that%20the%2040-year-old%20man%20from%20Idaho%20drunkenly%20harassed%20a%20herd%20of%20bison%20in%20Yellowstone%20and%20received%20minor%20injuries%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fyell%2Flearn%2Fnews%2F240429.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20NPS%20said%20the%20individual%20kicked%20one%20of%20the%20bison%20in%20the%20leg.%20He%20was%20ultimately%20charged%20and%20arrested%20in%20connection%20to%20the%20incident%2C%20which%20included%20being%20under%20the%20influence%20%26quot%3Bto%20a%20degree%20that%20may%20endanger%20oneself%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdisturbing%20wildlife.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20was%20the%20first%20involving%20bison%20in%20a%20national%20park%20this%20year.%20But%20the%20man%20can%20count%20himself%20lucky%20his%20injuries%20were%20minor.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20early%20June%2C%20the%20NPS%20reported%20an%2083-year-old%20South%20Carolina%20woman%20was%20gored%20and%20lifted%20a%20foot%20off%20the%20ground%20by%20a%20bison%20in%20Yellowstone%20National%20Park%2C%20leaving%20her%20with%20serious%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20NPS%20advises%20that%20visitors%20stay%20at%20least%2025%20years%20away%20from%20bison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EA%20herd%20of%20bison%20charged%20at%20another%20group%20of%20tourists%20in%20Yellowstone.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225616%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yellowstone%20Bison%20shutterstock%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F527c06aa6bb3f7e53fdf173a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223744%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20Prince%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20video%20captured%20by%20Yellowstone%20tourist%20Adella%20Gonzalez%20and%20shared%20by%20Storyful%2C%20a%20herd%20of%20bison%20is%20filmed%20meandering%20along%20calmly%20until%20a%20group%20of%20tourists%20walk%20by%2C%20seemingly%20prompting%20them%20to%20charge%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fnation%2F2024%2F05%2F17%2Fherd-bison-charging-tourists-yellowstone-national-park-video%2F73733051007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSA%20Today%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20video%2C%20taken%20in%20May%2C%20a%20person%20is%20heard%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20that%20is%20very%20wise%2C%26quot%3B%20just%20as%20the%20herd%20began%20to%20charge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20noticed%20tourists%20getting%20very%20close%20to%20the%20bison%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20told%20Storyful%2C%20and%20then%20the%20animals%20%26quot%3Bbegan%20to%20get%20agitated%20and%20started%20running.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20putting%20your%20own%20life%20at%20risk%2C%20getting%20too%20close%20to%20bison%20can%20also%20endanger%20the%20animals%20themselves.%20In%202023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-bison-killed-yellowstone-visitor-picked-up-herd-rejected-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20bison%20calf%20had%20to%20be%20euthanized%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20park%20visitor%20lifted%20it%20out%20of%20a%20river%2C%20causing%20it%20to%20be%20rejected%20by%20its%20herd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20shared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FYellowstoneNPS%2Fstatus%2F1661151420392013826%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20NPS%20said%20it%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20quarantine%20the%20calf%20and%20that%20it%20did%20not%20make%20the%20decision%20lightly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20made%20the%20choice%20we%20did%20not%20because%20we%20are%20lazy%2C%20uncaring%2C%20or%20inexpert%20in%20our%20understanding%20of%20bison%20biology%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20read.%20%26quot%3BWe%20made%20the%20choice%20we%20did%20because%20national%20parks%20preserve%20natural%20processes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIn%20June%2C%20a%20man%20was%20sentenced%20to%20a%20week%20in%20jail%20after%20trespassing%20dangerously%20close%20to%20a%20thermal%20geyser%20in%20Yellowstone%20National%20Park.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Steamboat%20Geyser%20in%20the%20Norris%20geyser%20basin%20in%20Yellowstone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66707ab8ed9a404d829e6993%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20man%20who%20trespassed%20into%20the%20geyser%20also%20received%20a%20two-year%20ban%20from%20Yellowstone%20National%20Park.%3Cp%3Efitopardo%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%2013%2C%20the%20NPS%20shared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fyell%2Flearn%2Fnews%2F24022.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%2021-year-old%20man%20from%20Washington%20received%20a%20weeklong%20jail%20sentence%20for%20venturing%20dangerously%20close%20to%20a%20steam%20vent%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nps.gov%2Fplaces%2F000%2Fsteamboat-geyser.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYellowstone%20National%20Park's%20Steamboat%20Geyser%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20world's%20tallest%20active%20geyser.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20man%2C%20who%20was%20caught%20on%20camera%20in%20April%2C%20hopped%20over%20a%20fence%20separating%20the%20geyser's%20steam%20vent%20from%20an%20observation%20point%20and%20got%20within%2015%20to%2020%20feet%20of%20it.%20According%20to%20the%20NPS%20website%2C%20the%20Steamboat%20Geyser%20erupts%20unpredictably%2C%20shooting%20hydrothermal%20water%20and%20steam%20that%20can%20cause%20severe%20burns%20up%20to%20300%20feet%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20Yellowstone%20National%20Park%20law%20enforcement%20officer%20arrived%20at%20the%20scene%2C%20the%20man%20told%20them%20he%20had%20gotten%20as%20close%20as%20he%20did%20to%20take%20photos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20jail%20time%2C%20the%20man%20was%20barred%20from%20visiting%20Yellowstone%20for%20two%20years%20and%20ordered%20to%20pay%20a%20%241%2C500%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20magistrate%20judge%20presiding%20over%20the%20case%20told%20the%20court%20that%20she%20hoped%20the%20sentence%20would%20prevent%20other%20visitors%20from%20figuratively%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20and%20literally%20%E2%80%94%20following%20in%20the%20man's%20footsteps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20expressed%20her%20concern%20that%20the%20defendant's%20actions%20were%20seen%20by%20the%20people%20around%20him%2C%20and%20they%20might%20have%20thought%20it%20was%20okay%20to%20do%20the%20same%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20press%20release%20noted.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20every%20visitor%20to%20YNP%20disobeyed%20the%20rules%2C%20the%20park%20would%20be%20destroyed%2C%20and%20no%20one%20would%20be%20able%20to%20enjoy%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftimes-tourists-behaved-badly-in-us-national-parks-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718792581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66706792e079049018199f2f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftimes-tourists-behaved-badly-in-us-national-parks-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20tourists%20have%20gotten%20into%20hot%20water%20in%20America's%20national%20parks%2C%20from%20close%20encounters%20with%20wild%20animals%20to%20mishandling%20historical%20artifacts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mnoyen%40insider.com%20(Maria%20Noyen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftimes-tourists-behaved-badly-in-us-national-parks-2024-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222%20Terrorists%20Killed%20In%20Encounter%20In%20Jammu%20And%20Kashmir's%20Baramulla%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETwo%20terrorists%20have%20been%20killed%20in%20a%20fierce%20encounter%20that%20broke%20out%20today%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20Hadipora%20village%20in%20the%20Baramulla%20distric