ar%20term%20allows%20you%20to%20spread%20out%20your%20payments%20over%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time%2C%20meaning%20you%20can%20keep%20your%20monthly%20payments%20lower%20and%20more%20manageable.%20The%20trade-off%20is%20that%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20you%20would%20with%20shorter%20terms%20or%20adjustable%20rates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E15-Year%20Fixed%20Mortgage%20Rates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F15-year-mortgage-rates%5C%22%3E15-year%20mortgage%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%206.17%25%2C%20a%2012-basis-point%20decrease%20from%20the%20previous%20week%2C%20according%20to%20Freddie%20Mac%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20the%20predictability%20that%20comes%20with%20a%20fixed%20rate%20but%20are%20looking%20to%20spend%20less%20on%20interest%20over%20the%20life%20of%20your%20loan%2C%20a%2015-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20might%20be%20a%20good%20fit%20for%20you.%20Because%20these%20terms%20are%20shorter%20and%20have%20lower%20rates%20than%2030-year%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20you%20could%20potentially%20save%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20interest.%20However%2C%20you'll%20have%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment%20than%20you%20would%20with%20a%20longer%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%20Down%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20started%20ticking%20up%20from%20historic%20lows%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202021%20and%20increased%20over%20three%20percentage%20points%20in%202022.%20Rates%20also%20increased%20dramatically%20last%20year%2C%20though%20they%20trended%20back%20down%20toward%20the%20end%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20inflation%20comes%20down%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20recede%20as%20well.%20Most%20major%20forecasts%20expect%20rates%20to%20go%20down%20later%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20homeowners%20looking%20to%C2%A0leverage%20their%20home's%20value%C2%A0to%20cover%20a%20big%20purchase%20%