in%20policies%20in%20the%20hopes%20of%20reversing%20the%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Tokyo%2C%20the%20rates%20are%20so%20low%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokyo-government-launching-dating-app-marriage-rates-population-decline-japan-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20is%20launching%20a%20dating%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20citizens%20find%20love%20and%20get%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20government%20has%20also%20tried%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-birthrate-reaches-record-low-billions-spent-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20fertility%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20offering%20up%20to%20a%20year%20of%20parental%20leave%20and%20even%20cash%20incentives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20South%20Korea%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fsouth-koreas-fertility-rate-dropped-fresh-record-low-2023-2024-02-28%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eleast%20fertile%20country%20in%20the%20world%2C%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Seoul%20is%20offering%20people%20money%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Fsouth-koreas-fertility-rate-dropped-fresh-record-low-2023-2024-02-28%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereverse%20their%20vasectomies%20or%20untie%20their%20tubes.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20on%20top%20of%20South%20Korean%20companies%20offering%20employees%20up%20to%20%2475%2C000%20to%20have%20children%2C%20and%20a%20government%20allowance%20system%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-parents-south-korea-seoul-750-per-month-population-declines-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egives%20all%20parents%20with%20newborns%20%24750%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20until%20their%20baby%20turns%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20according%20to%20Trent%20MacNamara%2C%20a%20Texas%20A%26amp%3BM%20professor%20whose%20work%20has%20focused%20on%20fertility%20rates%2C%20throwing%20money%20at%20the%20problem%20can%20only%20do%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheoretically%2C%20it's%20possible%20to%20produce%20higher%20fertility%20with%20traditional%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20a%20government%20transferred%20new%20parents%20about%205%25%20of%20the%20costs%20of%20raising%20a%20child%2C%20we%20could%20expect%20a%20roughly%205%25%20bump%20in%20fertility.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20noted%20that%20such%20measures%20come%20with%20%26quot%3Bbackbreaking%20costs%26quot%3B%20that%20governments%20are%20hesitant%20to%20bear%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20strain%20aging%20populations%20place%20on%20social%20welfare%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMacNamara%20said%20that%20even%20in%20countries%20like%20South%20Korea%2C%20which%20has%20invested%20billions%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20policies%20is%20still%20inconclusive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20governments%20are%20scrambling%20for%20solutions%2C%20none%20have%20discovered%20the%20holy%20grail%20%E2%80%94%20an%20affordable%2C%20practical%20policy%20leading%20to%20sustained%20fertility%20rate%20rises%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Harper%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20gerontology%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Oxford%20Institute%20of%20Population%20Ageing%2C%20says%20that%20cash%20incentives%20have%20a%20limited%20long-term%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20encourages%20a%20mini-baby%20boom%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20baby%20crash%2C%20as%20those%20women%20who%20would%20have%20spread%20their%20childbearing%20across%20several%20years%20all%20go%20at%20the%20same%20time%20to%20get%20the%20cash%20bonus%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarper%20said%20that%20instead%20of%20throwing%20money%20at%20the%20issue%2C%20the%20biggest%20chance%20for%20success%20is%20through%20promoting%20gender%20equity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20countries%20that%20promote%20%26quot%3Bpositive%20parenting%2C%20ensuring%20that%20mothers%2C%20as%20well%20as%20fathers%2C%20can%20continue%20their%20careers%20through%20acceptance%20in%20the%20workplace%2C%26quot%3B%20have%20the%20best%20chance%20of%20maintaining%20birth%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20added%20that%20even%20this%20is%20unlikely%20to%20return%20levels%20to%20above-replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhilip%20N.%20Cohen%2C%20a%20family%20demographer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%2C%20said%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bfool's%20errand%26quot%3B%20trying%20to%20solve%20the%20fertility%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20most%20policy%20ideas%20have%20failed%2C%20and%20besides%2C%20%26quot%3Bhuman%20history%20in%20the%20period%20of%20modernity%2C%20the%20last%20few%20hundred%20years%2C%20is%20the%20history%20of%20declining%20birth%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20unique%2C%20ambitious%20policy%20ideas%20could%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20make%20an%20impact%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20social%20welfare%20fund%20for%20single%20mothers%20and%20mass%20immigration%20from%20poorer%20countries%E2%80%94but%2C%20Cohen%20said%2C%20they're%20unlikely%20to%20be%20implemented%20in%20most%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20politically%20fraught%2C%20even%20if%20the%20math%20of%20it%20makes%20perfect%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20overall%20trend%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20way%20I%20think%20we%20can%20turn%20that%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthrowing-money-schemes-wont-solve-global-fertility-crisis-demography-experts-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718790758000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6666ec0ce079049018174e88%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%2