Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.gadgets360cdn.com%2Flarge%2Fcancer_pixabay_full_1555403784128.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20cancer%20burden%20is%20rising%20rapidly%2C%20but%20for%20a%20majority%20of%20Indians%2C%20cancer%20care%20is%20inaccessible%20and%20expensive%2C%20and%20disease%20detection%20late.%20In%202022%2C%20India%20had%20more%20than%2014.1%20lakh%20new%20cancer%20cases%20and%20over%209.1%20lakh%20deaths%20due%20to%20it%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO).%20As%20per%20reports%20published%20in%20February%202024%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20cancer%20before%20turning%2075%20in%20India%20was%2010.6%25.%20%C2%A0Also%2C%20seven%20out%20of%2010%20cancer%20patients%20in%20India%20die%20due%20to%20the%20disease.%20In%20developed%20nations%2C%20only%20three%20to%20four%20patients%20succumb%20to%20it.%20The%20reason%20for%20such%20high%20death%20rates%20is%20inadequate%20treatment%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20the%20infrastructure%20for%20cancer%20treatment%20is%20limited%20to%20just%20about%20100%20towns%20and%20cities.%20A%20major%20issue%20is%20that%20most%20of%20India's%20cancer%20patients%20stay%20in%20towns%20and%20rural%20areas%2C%20while%20the%20bulk%20of%20healthcare%20resources%20are%20in%20larger%20cities.%20In%20fact%2C%2040%25%20of%20the%20infrastructure%20for%20cancer%20care%20is%20concentrated%20in%20the%20top%2010%20metros.%20Naturally%2C%20on%20average%2C%20a%20cancer%20patient%20has%20to%20travel%20for%20six%20to%20seven%20hours%20to%20reach%20the%20nearest%20treatment%20facility.%20Healthcare%20experts%20also%20point%20out%20that%20making%20cancer%20drugs%20available%20in%20interior%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20is%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20tasks%20for%20the%20healthcare%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERuby%20Ahluwalia%2C%20founder%20of%20Sanjeevani%3A%20Life%20Beyond%20Cancer%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20provides%20care%2C%20counselling%20and%20rehabilitation%20to%20cancer%20patients%2C%20says%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20for%20a%20holistic%20support%20system%20for%20cancer%20patients.%20%26quot%3BThe%20doctor-patient%20ratio%20is%20approximately%201%3A2%2C000.%20Primary%20healthcare%20staff%20at%20government%20hospitals%20usually%20have%20little%20knowledge%20about%20cancer%20diagnosis.%20There%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20focus%20on%20spreading%20awareness%20about%20prevention%20and%20early%20detection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20Hospitals%20Need%20A%20Boost%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGovernment%20or%20public%20hospitals%20lack%20the%20infrastructure%20for%20cancer%20treatment.%20There%20are%20only%20around%205%2C000%20beds%20in%20government%20hospitals%20for%20lakhs%20of%20cancer%20patients.%20It's%20not%20uncommon%20to%20see%20long%20queues%20at%20hospitals%20like%20AIIMS.%20As%20per%20one%20report%2C%20at%20AIIMS%20Delhi%2C%20of%20the%2070%2C000%20cancer%20patients%20who%20register%20for%20treatment%2C%20only%2037%2C000%20are%20able%20to%20avail%20of%20it.%20Currently%2C%20there%20are%2025%20AIIMS%20hospitals%20in%20the%20country%2C%20of%20which%20only%2012%20are%20functional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20private%20hospitals%2C%20there%20are%20around%202%2C500%20beds%20assigned%20for%20cancer%20patients.%20At%20charitable%20institutes%20like%20Tata%20Memorial%2C%20Mumbai%2C%2070%25%20of%20patients%20are%20treated%20free%20of%20cost%20or%20at%20a%20nominal%20cost.%20Around%2065%2C000%20patients%20are%20treated%20on%20a%20yearly%20basis%20here.%20The%20Centre's%20initiative%20of%20pooled%20procurement%20of%20essential%20cancer%20medicines%20has%20led%20to%20around%2082%25%20cost%20savings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20all%2C%20roughly%20only%20around%2030%25%20of%20cancer%20patients%20are%20able%20to%20avail%20of%20treatment%20in%20government%20hospitals.%20The%20rest%20are%20left%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20private%20hospitals%2C%20or%20worse%2C%20nothing.%20%C2%A0%26quot%3BSadly%2C%20we%20still%20do%20not%20have%20sufficient%20hospitals%20in%20both%20government%20and%20private%20sectors%20to%20treat%20the%20burgeoning%20numbers%20of%20cancer%20patients.%20Many%20patients%20still%20have%20to%20travel%20to%20Tier-1%20cities%20for%20advanced%20treatment.%20We%20need%20comprehensive%20cancer%20care%20centres%20in%20districts%20to%20serve%20the%20population%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr%20Aditya%20Kulkarni%2C%20senior%20consultant%2C%20GI-%20Hepatobiliary%20Cancer%20Surgery%20and%20Robotic%20surgery%2C%20Ruby%20Hall%20Clinic%2C%20Pune.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20National%20Cancer%20Grid%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Cancer%20Grid%20(NCG)%20was%20set%20up%20in%20August%202012%20to%20link%20cancer%20care%20centres%20across%20India.%20The%20Central%20government-funded%20NCG%20had%20the%20primary%20mandate%20of%20working%20towards%20establishing%20uniform%20standards%20of%20care%20across%20the%20country%20by%20adopting%20evidence-based%20management%20guidelines%2C%20exchange%20of%20expertise%2C%20and%20collaborative%20research%20cross%20centres.%20As%20part%20of%20NCG%2C%20modern%20technology-based%20cancer%20treatment%20is%20available%20at%20298%20hospitals%20in%20the%20country%2C%20of%20which%20only%2050%20are%20government%20hospitals.%20The%20rest%20are%20run%20by%20private%20hospitals%20and%20trusts.%20This%20network%20treats%20over%20two-thirds%20of%20India's%20cancer%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Debilitating%20Costs%20Of%20Cancer%20Care%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20a%20large%20number%20of%20patients%20come%20from%20economically%20distressed%20backgrounds%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cancer%20drugs%20is%20a%20big%20deterrent%20to%20their%20access%20to%20high-quality%20treatment.%20As%20per%20a%20study%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cancer%20treatment%20on%20average%20is%20around%20Rs%2061%2C216%20per%20hospitalisation%20session.%20High%20out-of-pocket%20expenditure%20can%20result%20in%20calamitous%20spending%20for%20households%20and%20can%20potentially%20push%20families%20into%20poverty.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20in%20a%20country%20where%20a%20large%20segment%20of%20the%20population%20relies%20on%20daily%20wages%20or%20is%20part%20of%20the%20informal%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20American%20Society%20of%20Clinical%20Oncology%20Publications%2C%20approximately%2040%25%20of%20cancer%20costs%20are%20met%20through%20borrowing%2C%20sales%20of%20assets%2C%20and%20contributions%20from%20friends%20and%20relatives%3B%20these%20costs%20exceed%2020%25%20of%20the%20annual%20per%20capita%20household%20expenditure%20in%2060%25%20of%20Indian%20households%20that%20have%20a%20cancer%20patient.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERadiotherapy%20works%20well%20but%20is%20expensive.%20As%20per%20WHO%2C%20one%20tele-radiotherapy%20machine%20is%20required%20for%2010%20lakh%20population%20on%20average.%20As%20per%20that%20estimate%2C%20India%20should%20have%201%2C300%20machines%2C%20but%20it%20has%20only%20700.%20As%20many%20as%2070%25%20of%20cancer%20patients%20can%20be%20treated%20by%20radiotherapy.%20But%20since%20radiotherapy%20is%20expensive%2C%20only%2020%25%20of%20cancer%20patients%20are%20able%20to%20access%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20cost%20of%20cancer%20treatment%20depends%20on%20many%20factors%2C%20including%20the%20type%20of%20cancer%2C%20the%20stage%20of%20disease%20and%20the%20treatments%20needed.%20Advanced%20treatments%20like%20cyber%20knife%20radiosurgery%20or%20robotic%20surgery%20are%20costly%2C%20as%20are%20newer%20chemotherapy%20agents%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dr%20Kulkarni.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Ms.%20Ahluwalia%20rightly%20points%20out%2C%20%26quot%3BCancer%20is%20a%20diagnosis%20that%20opens%20up%20multiple%20fronts%20for%20a%20patient.%20All%20of%20them%20need%20to%20be%20addressed%20for%20the%20cancer%20experience%20to%20become%20easier.%20Medical%20treatment%20is%20just%20one%20of%20the%20tools%20required%20by%20a%20patient%20to%20get%20cured%20of%20cancer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20AIIMS%20and%20other%20government%20hospitals%2C%20the%20waiting%20period%20for%20patients%20has%20to%20be%20reduced.%20Treatment%20of%20patients%20needs%20to%20be%20prioritised%20based%20on%20the%20seriousness%20of%20their%20condition.%20Experts%20recommend%20establishing%20cancer%20care%20centres%20instead%20of%20cancer%20hospitals%20as%20they%20have%20specialists%20to%20address%20all%20fronts%20a%20cancer%20patient%20faces.%20Controlling%20the%20cost%20of%20cancer%20drugs%20and%20equipment%2C%20public-private%20partnerships%20in%20treatment%20and%20research%2C%20and%20addressing%20manpower%20shortages%20at%20primary%20health%20centres%20in%20villages%20and%20district%20headquarters%2C%20are%20some%20immediate%20steps%20that%20the%20Central%20and%20state%20governments%20have%20to%20take%20to%20arrest%20the%20tide.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20Contributing%20Editor%2C%20NDTV)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718786460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.gadgets360cdn.com%2Flarge%2Fcancer_pixabay_full_1555403784128.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-grim-cancer-reality-1-doctor-for-every-2-000-patients-5922536%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%202022%2C%20India%20had%20more%20than%2014.1%20lakh%20new%20cancer%20cases%20and%20over%209.1%20lakh%20deaths%20due%20to%20it%2C%20according%20to%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22